ENTRY            D6505   20260203   20260528   20260528       D152
SUBENT        D6505001   20260203   20260528   20260528       D152
BIB                 11         34
TITLE      Proton induced reaction on 108Cd for astrophysical
            p-process studies
AUTHOR     (S.Saha, D.Basak, T.Bar, L.K.Sahoo, J.Datta,
            S.Dasgupta, N.Kinoshita, C.Basu)
INSTITUTE  (3INDVEC)
           (3INDIND) Homi Bhabha National Institute,
            Anushaktinagar, Mumbai
           (2JPNJPN) Technology of Institute, Shimizu Corporation,
            Koto-ku, Tokyo
REFERENCE  (J,JP/G,52,065101,2025)
FACILITY   (CYCLO,3INDVEC) K-130 cyclotron
SAMPLE     (48-CD-108,ENR=0.663) Isotopically enriched 108Cd
            targets (38.7 mg) on Mylar (H8C10O4) backing were
            prepared using the vacuum evaporation technique.
            Eight different targets with thicknesses ranging from
            288 to 659 ug/cm2 were deposited on a 13 um Mylar
            backings.
           Aluminum foils (6.5 um, 12 um, 25 um and 100 um and
            99.95% pure) were used as energy degraders to reduce
            the proton beam energy before and within the target
DETECTOR   (HPGE) detector with 40% relative efficiency and energy
            resolution of 1.8 keV at 1.33 MeV gamma-ray energy.
METHOD     (ACTIV,BCINT) Targets were irradiated for 6-17 hrs with
            a proton beam of 150-200 nA.
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-T)  Total uncertainties are propagated from:
           Statistical uncertainty arises from the uncertainty in
            the peak counts of particular gamma-line.
           (ERR-S) Statistical uncertainty
           (ERR-SYS) Systematic uncertainty
           (ERR-1) Target thickness (~9%)
           (ERR-2) Detector efficiency (~6.4%)
           (ERR-3) Decay parameters from the literature (~4%)
STATUS     (TABLE,,S.Saha+,J,JP/G,52,065101,2025) Table 5
HISTORY    (20260203C) VT
ENDBIB              34
